** For Ubuntu/Debian (apt) ..

$ sudo apt-get update
$ sudo apt-get install git

* verification .

$ git --version

* Config Git UserName & Email .

$ git config --global user.name "foo"
$ git config --global user.email "foo@foo.com"

* For Example.

$ git config --global user.name "gk"
$ git config --global user.email "gk123@gmail.com"


** For Fedora (dnf/yum) .

$ sudo dnf install git
Or
$ sudo yum install git

* verification.

$ git --version

* Config Git user & email .

$ git config --global user.name "foo"
$ git config --global user.email "foo@foo.com"

* For example.

$ git config --global user.name "gk"
$ git config --global user.email "gk123@gmail.com"

** for older versions of Fedora...

$ sudo dnf install curl-devel expat-devel gettext-devel openssl-devel perl-devel zlib-devel asciidoc xmlto docbook2X


***Install git in Amazon EC2 instance...

$ sudo yum install git

* Verification

$ git version


** starting with Git....

* Create a directory 

$ mkdir mygit

* Get into the created directory

$ cd mygit/

* Now, initialize git local repository

$ git init


